---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Delete Your Account - Empire Inc"
  description="How to request deletion of your Empire Inc account and associated data"
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-white py-16 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Delete Your Empire Inc Account</h1>

      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> June 18, 2026
      </p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
        <section>
          <p>
            This page explains how to request deletion of your account and associated
            data for the <strong>Empire Inc</strong> mobile application, developed by Empire Inc.
            Account deletion is permanent and cannot be undone.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Option 1: Delete in the App (instant)</h2>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Open the <strong>Empire Inc</strong> app and sign in to your account</li>
            <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong></li>
            <li>Scroll to the account actions section and tap <strong>Delete Account</strong></li>
            <li>Confirm in the dialog by tapping <strong>Delete Forever</strong></li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Your account and all associated personal data are deleted immediately and permanently.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Option 2: Request by Email</h2>
          <p>
            If you cannot access the app, email
            <a href="mailto:privacy@empireinc.app" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">privacy@empireinc.app</a>
            from the email address associated with your account, with the subject
            <strong>"Delete my account"</strong>. We verify ownership and complete the
            deletion within <strong>30 days</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">What Data Is Deleted</h2>
          <p>When you delete your account, we permanently remove:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Your authentication record (email address and sign-in identity)</li>
            <li>Profile and display information</li>
            <li>Game progress, businesses, investments, and in-game balances</li>
            <li>Transactions, tax records, achievements, and skills</li>
            <li>Friends, clan membership, and any clan you own</li>
            <li>Advertising and analytics records tied to your account</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">What Data May Be Retained</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong>Encrypted backups:</strong> purged on our regular backup cycle, within
              <strong>30 days</strong> of deletion.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Purchase &amp; tax records:</strong> retained only where required by law
              (e.g. accounting and tax obligations), for the legally mandated period, and not
              used for any other purpose.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Aggregated, anonymized analytics</strong> that can no longer be linked to you.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Questions</h2>
          <p>
            For any questions about account or data deletion, contact
            <a href="mailto:privacy@empireinc.app" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">privacy@empireinc.app</a>.
            See also our
            <a href="https://empireinc.app/privacy" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-slate-800">
        <p class="text-slate-400">Empire Inc</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
